px:
   specify size directly in pixel.

    Even If the browser setting changes, it won't affect the size of that element


rem:
  specify the size in terms of root element(relative to root element)
  eg 1rem : 1 times the size of root element(HTML)
  We ca n have decimal values for this type

em :
  specift the size in term of parent element
  eg 2em means 2 times the size of parent element

vh:
   specify size in terms of height of view port
   It is in %factor
   If the viewport height changes, this value will also change.

vw:
   specify the size in terms of width of viewport
   It is in %factor
   If the viewport width changes, this value will also change.

%:
   if we use % for font size then it is the % of defaulf font size
